76561198004190775,Recommended,406310,21366963,"Posted: 21 February, 2016",all,MissMardybum,"I used to love playing this game as a kid, with a pen and paper at school during lunch.Still gets your brain going, as the theme can be made to be anything ie, something round, something you wear, something found in a kitchen......so has a new twist to it depending on the room creater.5 themes are chosen, then the computer will generate a random letter fastest to complete all 5, presses stop, BUT then all other players validate the answers given by ticking or unticking the boxes, so people with stupid/nonsence answers cant win. There are 10 letters generated/rounds per game, winner is collector of highest points from all 10 games combined.The only 2 negatives are ;1. not enough people playing it, sat for 30 mins and no-one came online !2. I think the price is steep for how simple the game is, if it was cheaper maybe more people would buy it and then we would get some games played !"
